From 8b994eea8f3031dfcdccfce9c0d6a1cb34ed58ce Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:26:39 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: wifi Adding new condition for ieee hardware 
 register

Bringup support for SLO mode with non-single wiphy architecture.
With non-single wiphy archtecture, all wiphy will hold only one radio interface for each
ath12k radio group.So, existing condition is changed during the ath12k mac hw register.

Signed-off-by: Gautham Kumar Senthilkumaran <quic_gauthamk@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 net/wireless/core.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/wireless/core.c b/net/wireless/core.c
index 6ec21de..3b40130 100644
--- a/net/wireless/core.c
+++ b/net/wireless/core.c
@@ -892,7 +892,7 @@ static int cfg80211_validate_per_hw_chans(struct wiphy *wiphy)
 	 * be sufficient
 	 */
 
-	if (wiphy->num_hw < 2)
+	if (wiphy->num_hw < 1)
 		return -EINVAL;
 
 	for (i = 0; i < wiphy->num_hw; i++) {
-- 
2.34.1

